    {
      "id": "advanced-primitives-reader",
      "type": "port",
      "label": "Advanced Reader Port",
      "position": {
        "x": -760,
        "y": -200
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-advanced-primitives"
        },
        "view": {
          "intent": "node",
          "payload": "node.web.detail"
        },
        "renderShape": {
          "kind": "markdown"
        },
        "markdown": "# Advanced Reader Port\n\nThis node is the declared reading surface for the advanced primitives tutorial.\n\nAdvanced primitives still follow the same surface rule as the basic ones:\n- create the port node\n- expose it in the declaration\n- bind the declaration surface to the port node id\n\n`bridge`, `script`, and `field` are more advanced, but they still show up through ordinary declared graph surfaces."
      }
    },
